description: Western Alaska Minerals Corp. engages in the development, exploration, and operation of mineral properties in the United States. The company primarily explores for gold, silver, copper, lead, and zinc deposits. It holds a 100% interest in the Illinois Creek mining district, which includes three distinct properties comprising Illinois Creek, Round Top, and Honker that consists of 222 mining claims covering an area of approximately 14,374 hectares located in the State of Alaska. The company is headquartered in Tucson, Arizona.
